5:
Claw, where are we meeting this friend 
of yours? We've strayed a long way 
from the village.
9:
Aaalmost there. 
We should see him any second now—
18:
Dog ears... Dog tail...
An ambush?!
23:
Whoa, whoa, hold on! This is that 
friend I told you about!
27: Sorry we kept you waiting, Albert.
31:
Everything's all done and dusted on 
my end, Claw. It won't be easy, but we 
can put the plan in motion whenever 
you're ready.
35:
This is your friend? You're workin' with 
the dogfolk?
39:
Ah, you must be Nimbus. Allow me to 
introduce myself. Albert Fang, Knight. 
I'm one of the castle guards.
41:
Color me surprised. You really DO look 
just like the stories.
44:
Hey, c'mon, I wouldn't lie to you, 
would I?
48:
You exaggerate everything. Shall I list 
all the times you've tried to sweettalk 
me into something?
52: So he WAS just buttering us up.
56:
*sigh* He has good intentions.
At any rate, we would like to ask 
Nimbus to meet with His Majesty—
the king of the dogfolk.
58:
He cannot possibly decline an 
audience with "Prince Whitetail."
62:
You guys really think he'll buy that 
I'm a prince?
67:
It'll be fiiine, man! You just stand there 
looking pretty and I'LL handle the 
talking.
74:
I'm a pretty smooth talker when I want 
to be! And, no offense, but it'd make 
things a heck of a lot easier for me if 
you just stay quiet.
78: I have a bad feeling about this…
81:
Oh, but I WOULD appreciate help 
taking out any monsters we run into!
84:
He sure knows how to boss a guy 
around, huh?
93:
I'll handle the monsters.
Come along, now. We've still a ways 
to the castle.
95:
Many of the dogfolk are keen to see 
this war ended—for good and for all. 
I implore you to lend us your aid, 
Nimbus.
